
SmokeTest

Testcase to verify the providers can be loaded and used.  The use is very simple, just enough to know it worked. The test
uses the FFM providers.

EQ.  I used a T-cobbler plugged into a prototype board, two BMP280 sensors, both mounted on individual breakout boards.
Connections are M-M jumpers.  The I2C and SPI BMP280 charts refers to connection points on the breakout board but your sensor
may use different letter designations. Also, the are BMP sensors available with I2C and SPI interfaces or only one of
the interfaces, read the fine print if you order these sensors.

The PWM, Input, output and Serial charts are M-M jumpers between T-cobbler pins.

I2C   BMP280

| RPi        | Color  | Sensor |
|:-----------|:-------|:-------|
| Pin1  3.3V | 	Red   | Vin    |
| N/C        |        | 3v	    |
| Pin6  Gnd  | Black  | Gnd    |
| Pin5  SCL  | Yellow | SCK    |
| N/C        |        | SDO    |
| Pin3  SDA  | Orange | SDA    |
| Pin17 3.3v | Red    | CS     |



SPI BMP280
connection using 4-wire SPI

| RPi            | Color  | Sensor  |
|:---------------|:-------|:--------|
| Pin19 MOSI     | Blue   | SDA     |
| Pin21 MISO     | Purple | SDO     |
| Pin23 SCLK     | Green  | SCK/SCL |
| Pin24 SPICE0   | Yellow | CS      |
| Pin6  Gnd      | Black  | GND     |
| Pin1  3.3V     | Red    | Vin/Vcc |



PWM
| RPi                | Color  |    Monitor     |
|:-------------------|:-------|:---------------|
| Pin12  GPIO18 PWM  | Green  | Pin16  GPIO23  |


Output
| RPi                   | Color  |     Monitor    |
|:----------------------|:-------|:---------------|
| Pin18  GPIO24 Output  | Blue   | Pin22  GPIO25  |

Input
| RPi                   | Color  |     Control    |
|:----------------------|:-------|:---------------|
| Pin36  GPIO16 Input   | Green  | Pin37  GPIO26  |


Serial
| RPi                   | Color  | Sensor  |
|:----------------------|:-------|:--------|
| Pin8   GPIO14 TX      | White  | loopback|
| Pin10  GPIO15 RX      | White  | loopback|
+
